    <note>Zhang(1) Guang [13974] Failed the jinshi exams and then used the yin of his uncle to enter the civil service. According to his wife's funerary inscription (on which his basic biography is based), he was a man from Jin, which is a generic name for Shanxi or, sometimes, Northwest China. He has the same generational name as Zhang(1) Guan [7158], who is son of Yu(2) [7175] and grandson of Shunmin [291]. It is also consistant with chronological logic that Guan and Guang are cousins. Finally, Lu(5) You did the funerary inscription for Guan and also for Guang's wife, Fei(1) Shu's [13977] daughter.  SHY:ZG, 72.25b-26a; Lu You, WJ, 32.4a-4b (wife, born Fei(1), who married him at age 17 and died in 1172 at age 55).From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1179:  Dismissed (fangba) as Hubei yunpan.</note>
